# macOS Finder duplicates — `Foo 2.swift`/`Foo 2/` are produced when a
# file or folder is duplicated in Finder; same-module redeclarations
# break `swift build` with ambiguous-symbol errors. Ignored so a Finder
# slip can't blow up the build silently again. (Resolved en masse on
# 2026-05-04 via the workspace-hygiene round; see
# spec/autonomous/backlog/workspace-hygiene-finder-duplicate-source-files-2026-05-04.md.)
* 2.swift
* 2.md
* 2.sh
* 2.py
* 2/
